snippet.textDisplay: Please please guys stop having guests that worked on the films you review for so many of these CGI clips. You rarely EVER say anything bad or judgemental of the clips, only praising him and mostly just watching the shots while he explains. There's so much behind the scenes stuff for movies already and you guys are already professionals in our eyes. We want Clint's fake puking, Niko's smirk as he explains what went wrong, Wren guessing what they did and looking at Niko to see if he agrees. People thought these were so incredibly hilarious, it's awesome to hear what the experts have to say but you guys are already pro, this was like your show. You already had the expertise but now it feels like you're too many dicks on the dance floor and the humor is kind of gone (understandably, since you want relevant clips to who the guest is, the shots you pick are mostly awesome looking AND you wouldn't laugh in the face of the guy who was partially responsible for the job itself.) Thank you guys, this serie of reacting to bad & great CGi is probably my favourite series on youtube hands down. So f'ing funny
